05/01/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- In a retrial of their case, the Skopje Court on Thursday (January 4th) sentenced former Defence Minister Ljuben Paunovski and a relative, Ljupcho Petkovski, to three and half years in prison for embezzlement.
The retrial cut Paunovski's initial sentence by two years.
The sentences of co-defendants Kiril Gorgov and Vladimir Talevski were reduced from two and a half years to one year each.
The court also ordered Paunovski to return 1.5m euros to the defence ministry.
(Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 04/01/07)
